Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.21,0:01:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ironwood on P.A.]\NCitizens of Mantle:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.54,0:01:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Following the most recent Grimm attack,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.66,0:02:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,a temporary prohibition of\Nassembly is now in effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.83,0:02:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There are to be no public\Ngatherings of any kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.75,0:02:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Please conduct your business
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.00,0:02:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and return to your homes before curfew.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.33,0:02:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This is for your own safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.29,0:02:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Patrol] Hey, stop right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.33,0:02:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop running! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.66,0:02:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Newscaster] Though military officials
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.62,0:02:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,have gone on record to say\Nthe footage was doctored,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.91,0:02:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,many citizens are still insisting that the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.16,0:02:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Protector of Mantle be deactivated.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.29,0:02:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Driver] Civilian,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.12,0:02:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you are obstructing an\NAtlas military operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.08,0:02:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, step aside.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.58,0:02:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Soldier] Everything\Nall right over here?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.00,0:02:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.25,0:03:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ironwood] This is\Nthe worst case scenario.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.37,0:03:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,More people are dead, Penny's been framed,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.25,0:03:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and somehow, Jacques Schnee\Nis sitting on the council.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.87,0:03:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's the second shipment
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.00,0:03:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,for Amity that was hit today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.79,0:03:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems election night was the last push
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.66,0:03:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Robyn needed to go from hometown hero
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.62,0:03:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to full-on vigilante.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.21,0:03:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm afraid the problem
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.33,0:03:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,is more complicated than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.50,0:03:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ironwood] It seems Robyn has emboldened
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.21,0:03:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,our suppliers in Mantle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.75,0:03:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They're refusing to sell us provisions
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.21,0:03:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,until the city is adequately repaired.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.71,0:03:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,With Robyn redistributing the\Ngoods her team has stolen,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.96,0:03:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the Amity Project is completely stalled.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.00,0:03:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ruby] But we're so close.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.21,0:03:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,There has to be some way\Nwe can finish the tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.37,0:04:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- There is: declaring martial law.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.16,0:04:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Nora] You're not actually\Nconsidering that, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.08,0:04:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ironwood] What's more important?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.66,0:04:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Establishing communications,\Nunite the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.41,0:04:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Or appeasing a few city blocks?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.16,0:04:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Nora] Don't make is sound trivial
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.37,0:04:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,when you know it isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.29,0:04:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You keep talking about how we\Njust need a little more time,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.29,0:04:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're not the one having to struggle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.91,0:04:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ironwood] We have all\Nhad to make sacrifices
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.58,0:04:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,for the greater good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.21,0:04:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Mantle has had to bear a lot\Nof the burden, yes, but--
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.29,0:04:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- They're bearing all of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.87,0:04:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The longer this waiting game goes on,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.66,0:04:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the harder each day gets\Nfor people down there
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.04,0:04:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you wanna send in more soldiers?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.41,0:04:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't force people to fall in line.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.58,0:04:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do that, you'll just be trading
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.50,0:04:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,all of these problems for the Grimm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.71,0:04:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,- Please, General Ironwood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.66,0:04:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Squeezing Mantle this way...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.79,0:05:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That kind of division plays\Nright into Salem's hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.29,0:05:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why Tyrian is here framing you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.71,0:05:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Clover] Right, the reason we called
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.58,0:05:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you here in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.96,0:05:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You're sure this was the man you saw?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.83,0:05:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Winter] Tyrian Callows was accused
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.25,0:05:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,of murders all across Anima.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.29,0:05:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,A homicidal maniac who escaped justice
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.00,0:05:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,when his prison transport\Nwas attacked by Grimm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.71,0:05:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, he was never seen again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.66,0:05:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,- Well, he works for Salem and he's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.25,0:05:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- If we ever had any\Ndoubts Atlas was Salem's
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.54,0:05:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,next target, I think those\Nare officially out the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.62,0:05:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ruby] But now we have a suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.00,0:05:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We can tell the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.96,0:05:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- That a long-lost serial\Nkiller is loose in Mantle
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.79,0:05:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and the military has no idea where he is --
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.08,0:05:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,might make things worse\Nbefore they get better.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.16,0:05:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Nora] I am so sick of secrets!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.79,0:05:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If we just told everyone\Nabout Amity, about Salem --
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.58,0:05:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- We can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.29,0:05:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If we talk about Amity now,\Nwe risk Salem's forces,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.16,0:05:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,who we know are here,\Nworking to sabotage it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.87,0:05:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,If we tell them about\NSalem now, we risk falling
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.41,0:06:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Grimm before we\Ncan reunite Remnant.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.08,0:06:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to finish the tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.58,0:06:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I want Robyn Hill in custody.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.29,0:06:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We can offer her a deal if\Nshe gets Mantle to cooperate.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.46,0:06:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- We'll figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.54,0:06:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- Anyone not assisting with Robyn
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.87,0:06:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,needs to focus on Tyrian.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.58,0:06:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to know who he's working with,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.08,0:06:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,where he's hiding, what he's planning,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.33,0:06:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and how exactly that video of\NPenny got all over my kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.21,0:06:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Do I make myself clear?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.58,0:06:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Everyone] Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.16,0:06:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ren] Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.37,0:06:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Yang] Looks like\Nwe're approaching 51st.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.75,0:06:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Clover] Thanks for the\Nassist on this, you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.79,0:06:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we may all be split\Nbetween different trucks,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.33,0:06:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,but we need to be ready to act as one
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.91,0:06:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,in case Robyn's team takes the bait.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.08,0:06:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,If your truck is hit, pursue immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.83,0:06:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone else will move\Nin as fast as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.62,0:06:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Going radio silent. Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.96,0:06:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- Do you...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.04,0:07:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think we should've\Ntold Ironwood about Salem,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.54,0:07:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,before he put so much\Non the line for Amity?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.37,0:07:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- Sounds like you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.50,0:07:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,- I trust Ruby, but I\Nthink he deserves to know
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.46,0:07:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,what he's stepping into.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.96,0:07:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We all did.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.96,0:07:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.83,0:07:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- Look around.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.25,0:07:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The embargo, the military presence,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.46,0:07:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the restrictions on assembly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.41,0:07:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a bit prone to overreacting.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.75,0:07:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah, hard to argue with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.71,0:07:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, he didn't have\Na lot of good options.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.41,0:07:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm not sure there are\Nmany good options left
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.46,0:07:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,for any of us anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.58,0:07:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Keeping secrets, taking lives?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.62,0:07:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes you wonder how\Nfar we're gonna have to go
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.87,0:07:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep doing the right thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.33,0:07:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- Blake.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.37,0:07:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We did what we had to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.62,0:07:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,- I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.04,0:07:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But, next time, I wanna\Nmake sure we don't have to,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.87,0:07:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and I can tell you, ambushing\Na huntress who's just
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.83,0:08:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to help isn't an option\NI'm thrilled about choosing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.37,0:08:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- Then, maybe we shouldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.25,0:08:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ruby] How is she doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.46,0:08:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Pietro] She's confused, scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.04,0:08:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll have her recorded\Nvisual data shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.58,0:08:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That should prove her innocence,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.04,0:08:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but the damage has already been done.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.00,0:08:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The things people are saying about her...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.75,0:08:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If Penny hadn't been\Nthere, Robyn would be--
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.12,0:08:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- I don't think Robyn was their target.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.62,0:08:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Salem's goal has always been to divide us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.12,0:08:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I think Penny was exactly\Nwhere they wanted her,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.33,0:08:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,just like at the Vytal Festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.75,0:08:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- And just like back then,\Nsomeone is using our own
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.00,0:08:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,technology against us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.16,0:08:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,This doctored footage of Penny
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.79,0:08:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,came from her work all around Mantle,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.21,0:08:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,stolen straight from our\Nsurveillance network.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.12,0:08:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ugh, hacking, technology...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.41,0:08:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Why can't people just do what they used to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.25,0:09:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and fight to the death?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.71,0:09:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot simpler, if you ask me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.21,0:09:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,- Well, if we're dealing with\Nthe same enemy from Beacon,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.04,0:09:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,hacking into Mantle's\Nsystem would be simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.83,0:09:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Fortunately, the rest of Atlas
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.91,0:09:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is running on an upgraded network.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.04,0:09:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Weiss] And how would someone\Nget access to that network?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.96,0:09:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,- Well, only a few people have clearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.04,0:09:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Ironwood, the council, our cybersecurity
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.96,0:09:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and surveillance leads and\Nmaybe a select few who oversee
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.12,0:09:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,critical systems like\Nsewage or the heating grid.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.66,0:09:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- The heating grid run in partnership
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.33,0:09:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with the Schnee Dust Company.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.00,0:09:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- What are you thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.54,0:09:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- I don't know yet, but\Nsomething isn't right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.29,0:09:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Maria] Understatement of the century.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.91,0:09:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- And how are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.33,0:09:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- If Maria hadn't offered\Nto help me these past weeks,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.33,0:09:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd have likely collapsed by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.79,0:09:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Getting a communications\Ntower into the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.16,0:09:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,seems impossible on its own,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.00,0:09:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,but now, to think of what\Npeople wanna do to my girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.54,0:10:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- Even if the worst does happen,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.91,0:10:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you can always reactivate her again,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.21,0:10:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so maybe try not to worry so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.62,0:10:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- There's a reason why Penny\Nis the only one of her kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.16,0:10:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,When the General first challenged us
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.87,0:10:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to find the next breakthrough\Nin defense technology,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.08,0:10:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,most of my colleagues\Npursued more obvious choices.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.08,0:10:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I was one of the few who believed
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.83,0:10:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,in looking inward for inspiration.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.29,0:10:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- You wanted a protector with a soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.58,0:10:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,- I did. And when General\NIronwood saw her, he did too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.62,0:10:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Much to my surprise, the Penny Project
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.12,0:10:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,was chosen over all the other proposals.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.87,0:10:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- Why would you be surprised?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.50,0:10:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You created an artificial aura.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.08,0:10:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- Well, not quite.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.16,0:10:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- You gave her part of yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.79,0:11:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yes, and each time I rebuild Penny,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.75,0:11:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,it takes a little more.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.21,0:11:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If the people get their\Nwish and she's destroyed,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.66,0:11:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't be able to...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.71,0:11:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ruby] We'll find whoever's responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.71,0:11:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.00,0:11:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Yang] Robyn--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.91,0:11:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Robyn] Scramble!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.75,0:11:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Blake] No, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.37,0:11:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Robyn] Split up, and\Nregroup at the hideout.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.12,0:11:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Blake] Please stop, we just want to--
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.16,0:12:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,- If Ironwood wants me,\Nhe'll have to send more
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.00,0:12:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,than a couple of kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.25,0:12:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Yang] He is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.25,0:12:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Stopping the trucks alerted the Ace Ops.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.21,0:12:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have long before they arrive,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.00,0:12:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,so please listen to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.87,0:12:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to know the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.84,0:12:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,- You're stalling.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.77,0:12:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- Amity Colosseum, all these\Nsupplies, they're for...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.83,0:12:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,They're for a new communications tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.71,0:12:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- That doesn't make any sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.41,0:12:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,- A new tower means the\Nkingdoms can finally--
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.04,0:12:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- I know what the tower means, Fisticuffs.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.46,0:12:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,One of you take my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.16,0:12:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,- What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.00,0:12:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- You said time is short.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.33,0:12:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Either take it, or I'm gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.46,0:13:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me again, what is Ironwood\Nbuilding out in the tundra?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.33,0:13:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- A new communications tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.50,0:13:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He's trying to help everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.62,0:13:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- You're telling the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.12,0:13:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- Handy semblance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.33,0:13:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- Why keep that a secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.00,0:13:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- Because he doesn't\Nknow who he can trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.79,0:13:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Atlas isn't out to get anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.12,0:13:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The people murdering civilians in Mantle
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.08,0:13:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,are just trying to make it look that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.08,0:13:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And if those same people\Nlearn about Amity,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.08,0:13:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,they'd do everything in\Ntheir power to destroy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.29,0:13:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,- So, who are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.66,0:13:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's actually behind this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.25,0:13:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Harriet] Yang, Blake,\Nwhere are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.75,0:13:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,- We can't tell you that part yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.88,0:13:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ugh, bullsh--
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.59,0:13:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- Look, we are trusting\Nyou, so trust us when we say
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.16,0:13:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that Amity Tower needs to\Nstay a secret until it's done.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.50,0:13:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We just need a little more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.91,0:13:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Soldiers] This way, come on, over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.04,0:13:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We saw them over this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.50,0:13:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,- Run, we'll throw them off.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.58,0:13:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- I won't stop until I\Nknow the whole truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.50,0:14:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ironwood] It's right behind that door.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.87,0:14:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Oscar] The Staff of Creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.29,0:14:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ironwood] I hoped\Nbringing you down here
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.12,0:14:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,might jog some memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.75,0:14:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, it was your\Nidea to use the staff
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.21,0:14:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to lift Atlas off the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.29,0:14:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,- I thought gravity\Ndust kept Atlas afloat?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.08,0:14:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ironwood] Eh, that's the public story.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.41,0:14:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But with the staff, we have a constant,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.41,0:14:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,seemingly limitless energy source.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.25,0:14:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Oz once speculated it could\Ntake us as high as we wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.79,0:14:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,To tell you the truth, that served as
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.79,0:14:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the inspiration for the Amity Project.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.87,0:14:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Get a communication tower up in the sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.87,0:14:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,higher than the Grimm can survive
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.41,0:14:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,so we never lose contact\Nwith each other again.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.87,0:14:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Oscar] But, you're not\Nusing the staff to raise Amity.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.58,0:14:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- The staff can only be used\Nfor one purpose at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.62,0:14:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to have to do Amity
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.62,0:14:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the old-fashioned way, dust and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.71,0:14:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Oscar] It feels strange,\Nknowing that part of me
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.04,0:14:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,helped come up with all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.79,0:15:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ironwood] You'll get\Nused to it, I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.00,0:15:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, you won't even\Nknow who's who anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.75,0:15:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.16,0:15:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- We didn't always see eye to eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.54,0:15:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,but I wish I could ask Ozpin
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.33,0:15:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,what he thought of all of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.41,0:15:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,- Well, I can tell you what I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.33,0:15:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The path you're heading down\Nwhere you're the only one
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.08,0:15:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,with the answers, where you do the thing
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.41,0:15:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,you think is right no matter the cost,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.83,0:15:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not going to take you anywhere good.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.91,0:15:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- We have to stop Salem,\Nnothing matters more.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.25,0:15:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,- Some things matter more, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.91,0:15:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Keeping our humanity. It's what\Nmakes us different from her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.91,0:15:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- Sometimes I worry that's\Nher greatest advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.46,0:15:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Without humanity, does\Nshe still feel fear?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.41,0:15:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Does she ever hesitate?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.79,0:16:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,When Salem hit Beacon,\Neven with all my ships,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.37,0:16:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,all of my soldiers, I\Nwas no match for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.58,0:16:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never felt so helpless,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.03,0:16:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the way she told me she was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.58,0:16:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Oscar] It's okay to be afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.00,0:16:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You just can't let that fear control you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.33,0:16:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ironwood] I am not going\Nto end up like Lionheart.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.21,0:16:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you believe in me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.21,0:16:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,- I do believe in you,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.04,0:16:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,but not only you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.91,0:16:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the best thing\Nyou could do is sit down
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.33,0:16:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and talk with the people\Nyou're most afraid to.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.83,0:16:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- Now you are starting to sound like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.12,0:17:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ironwood] Winter, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.21,0:17:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,- What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.12,0:17:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- It looks like you're getting your wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.25,0:17:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- My father's first act.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.79,0:17:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We've all been invited to\Ndinner where the General
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.58,0:17:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,will be defending his seat on the Council.
